{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~amrm/slides/compiler/compiler/sld019.htm", "content": "\n<!--  Presentation generated by Internet Assistant for Microsoft PowerPoint 97 -->\n\n<HTML>\n<HEAD>\n\n<meta name=\"GENERATOR\" content=\"Microsoft Internet Assistant for Microsoft PowerPoint 97\">\n <TITLE>Features of the ADL</TITLE> \n</HEAD>\n\n<BODY     >\n\n<CENTER>\n<TABLE WIDTH=100%> \n     <TR> <TD WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER>\n         <IMG SRC=\"img019.gif\" usemap=\"#Objmap\" WIDTH=640 HEIGHT=480 BORDER=0>\n     </TD> </TR>\n     <TR> <TD WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER>\n         <A HREF=\"sld001.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"first.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"First\"></A>\n         <A HREF=\"sld018.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"prev.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Previous\"></A>\n         <A HREF=\"sld020.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"next.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Next\"></A>\n         <A HREF=\"sld024.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"last.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Last\"></A>\n         <IMG SRC=\"space.gif\" BORDER=0>\n         <A HREF=\"index.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"info.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Index\"></A>\n         <A HREF=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~nicolau\"><IMG SRC=\"home.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Home\"></A>\n         <A HREF=\"tsld019.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"text.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Text\"></A>\n     </TD> </TR>\n</TABLE>\n<P>Slide 19 of 24</P>\n</CENTER>\n<!-- <UL>\n<H2>Features of the ADL</H2>\n</UL></P>\n<P><UL>\n<LI><H2>The ADL has two major components:\n</H2>\n<UL>\n<LI>Description of the structure of the architecture.\n<UL>\n<LI> The individual components that make up the architecture\n<UL>\n<LI>datapath units, storage units, connections and ports.\n</UL><LI> The connectivity between these components\n<LI> Memory hierarchy\n</UL><LI>Description of the instruction-set of the architecture.\n<UL>\n<LI> Syntax and Semantics of the operations\n<LI> Constraints on parallelism between operations\n<LI> Information needed by the optimizations.\n</UL></UL></UL><UL>\n<LI><H2>Unlike previous ADLs ours tightly integrates the structural and instruction-set descriptions, reducing complexity and improving readability/usability.</H2>\n</UL></P>\n<P>  -->\n</Body>\n</HTML>\n", "encoding": "ascii"}